<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<strong><a class="nonexistent" href="./RedNaga">RedNaga</a></strong>: i was wearing a Cursed ring (i mean the ego type that recurse itself after a while) and after casting a remove curse i noticed that the cursed status disappeared from the character screen, even after the ring re-cursed itself.<br>
 As a side note, shouldn't the re-cursing feature be listed as well in the flags, along with cursed, aggravating, and the others? <p>
Simon: I see the new warning message... laugh... "Oops! It feels deathly cold... again!!" 
</p>
<p>
Afterall we get a curse flag when we put them on, and when we try to remove it. The curse should be obvious just by wearing the re-cursed stuff I think. 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a class="nonexistent" href="./RedNaga">RedNaga</a></strong>: I was talking about flag list in Character screen, not a message for when the item re-curse itself (though it may not be such a bad idea, after all) nor an inscription.<br>
 As for the obviousness, well, it <strong>is</strong> obvious, but so are additional speed, light and some other characteristic. I think the flag should be listed for completeness, also because some artifact may have this feature without it being obvious in their name. 
</p>
